Headline: Bus Substitution Between Illinois Medical District and UIC-Halsted
ShortDescription: Shuttle buses replace Blue Line service between Illinois Medical District and UIC-Halsted.

FullDescription.#cdata-section:
How does this affect my trip?
Shuttle buses replace rail service between Illinois Medical District and UIC-Halsted.

Trains will run between O’Hare and UIC-Halsted, and between Forest Park and Illinois Medical District.

Allow extra travel time.

Why is service being changed?
We are performing construction at the Racine Blue Line station and Morgan substation.

MAP

Headline: Blue Line Delays
ShortDescription: Blue Line trains running w/residual delays & congestion following an earlier unauthorized person on the tracks at Pulaski. Service resuming, allow extra time

FullDescription.#cdata-section:
Blue Line trains are running with residual delays and congestion following an earlier unauthorized person on the tracks at Pulaski.

Some trains and platforms may be busier than usual as crews work to restore normal service.

Trains are moving and normal service is being restored.

Allow extra travel time.
